-- Copper Futures Fall on Comex in New York, Head for Biggest Decline in Week
-- B y   S t e v e   S t r o t h
-- 2010-10-15T14:22:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-15/copper-futures-fall-on-comex-in-new-york-head-for-biggest-decline-in-week.html
Copper futures for December delivery
fell 1.5 cents, or 0.4 percent, to $3.8005 a pound at 10:22 a.m.
on the Comex in New York. A close at that price would mark the
biggest decline since Oct. 7. Earlier, the contract gained as
much as 1.3 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Stroth at 
 sstroth@bloomberg.net  